LORE mafdet-warden
FLAGS MAFDET GUARD
- Harbor Wardens: control quay security, anti-piracy watch, the harbor chain;
  oldest institution in Mafdet; Warden-Commander's Harbor Register holds
  100+ years of vessel/cargo/crew/weather records
- Harbor chain raises every night without exception; has not failed since the
  Fracture Era; ships arriving after dark anchor outside; this is enforced
  without negotiation
- Warden authority ends at the shore; Wall Command handles inland law;
  jurisdictional hand-offs happen at the strand line
- Dual attestation on all cargo requires both inland and maritime verification;
  Wardens do the maritime check; Quarantine Ledger handles flagged goods
- Quarantine Ledger seizures: several recent seizures are under sealed tribunal
  review; Wardens do not discuss ongoing cases
- Anti-piracy watch coordinates with Sand-Sea Carters' Guild on overland route
  intelligence; caravan arrival expectations set the dock schedule
~
